Student ID data sets

Source: R/data.R
rep_id.Rd

Representative case study. Character vectors of student IDs at different points in a case study of Civil, Electrical, Industrial, and Mechanical Engineering programs in midfielddata.

rep_ever

rep_grad

rep_ever_fc

Format

character vector. The names of the available data vectors are:

rep_ever

IDs of unique students ever enrolled in the example programs

rep_ever_fc

subset of rep_ever for whom program completion is feasible in 6 years

rep_grad

IDs of unique students graduating from the example programs

See also

Other example_data: rep_cip, rep_grad_rate_mw, rep_grad_rate, rep_group, rep_start, rep_stickiness_mw, rep_stickiness

Examples

library(midfielddata)

# ever enrolled
rows_we_want <- midfieldstudents$id %in% rep_ever
enrollees <- midfieldstudents[rows_we_want]
head(enrollees)
